'''Batter boards''' (or ''battre boards'', Sometimes mispronounced as "battle boads") are temporary [[framing (construction)|frames]], set beyond the corners of a planned [[Foundation (construction)|foundation]] at precise elevations. These batter boards<ref>http://www.dictionaryofconstruction.com/definition/batter-boards.html</ref> are then used to hold [[layout line]]s (construction twine) to indicate the limits<ref>http://homeguides.sfgate.com/purpose-batter-boards-laying-foundation-76196.html</ref> (edges and corners) of the foundation.
[[File:Batter-Boards with-Strings.jpg|thumb|Batter Boards for a 16' x 16' foundation]]
[[File:Strings-at-batter-boards.jpg|thumb|View of crossed strings at batter boards. indicating corner of foundation.]]

