'''Configurable Mixed-signal IC''' (abbreviated as '''CMIC''') is a category of ICs comprising a matrix of analog and digital blocks which are configurable through programmable (OTP) non-volatile memory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.analog-eetimes.com/news/silego-scaling-cost-effective-agility-mixed-signal|title=Silego scaling cost-effective agility in mixed-signal|date=24 August 2016|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref><ref name="analog-eetimes.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.analog-eetimes.com/news/why-programmable-analog-themed-box-lego|title=Why programmable analog is like a themed box of Lego|date=24 August 2016|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref> The technology, in combination with its design software and development kits, allows immediate prototyping of custom mixed-signal circuits, as well as the integration of multiple discrete components into a single IC to reduce PCB cost, size and assembly issues.<ref>http://www.silego.com/uploads/Products/product_454/details/WP-1001%20ASM%20vs%20MCU%20App%20Article.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://electronicdesign.com/learning-resources/design-solutions|title=Design Solutions|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.embedded.com/electronics-blogs/max-unleashed-and-unfettered/4441933/ASM-vs--MCU-for-IoT--portable---wearable-applications|title=ASM vs. MCU for IoT, portable & wearable applications|first=Clive|last=Maxfield|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polyscope.ch/archiv/2016/10/freude-gross-a-reparaturkosten-klein_57364/|title=polyscope.ch > Archiv > 2016 > 10 >  Freude gross – Reparaturkosten klein|first=update|last=AG|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://powerelectronics.com/power-management/high-performance-reverse-blocking-pfet-integrated-power-controllers|title=High-Performance, Reverse-Blocking, pFET Integrated Power Controllers|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref>

